metadata.description:
Club LitterBox is a collection of 4,444 generative cat avatars, with over 100 hand-drawn features by Michael Moodie and 5 unreleased songs made by Felix Cartal, including 1 original and 4 remixes.
They look like productive members of society by day, but when night falls, these degens head to Happy Hour at Club LitterBox to indulge in catnip and killer tunes.
But the CLB isn't just a place to escape the fud of web2 life. From their dive bar, these cats are planning a takeover of the metaverse.
In addition to high-res art and quality music, each NFT grants unlimited song streaming and the commercial rights to the visual art.
Rare traits include Song Royalties and a Limited YouTube Music License, so content creators can use this music in videos and still monetize their work!
This collection was released on the Nota launchpad so holders will access presale draws and more utility revealed in the coming weeks
